No criminal record (excl. political in the previous dispensation). 

Primary Function: 
To provide strategic leadership on all aspects of integrated public safety, and to ensure efficient and effective implementation/performance of the core functions prescribed in Section 64C of the South African Police Service Act namely; traffic policing, by-law enforcement, and traffic management. 

Key Performance Areas: 
Lead the provision of policing, traffic management, by-law enforcement, and crime prevention services; 
Provision of assets, property, and human resources in order to ensure security services; 
Lead the provision of driver licensing and testing services; 
Lead and manage the Branch in terms of Section 64C (2) (a-h); 
Financial and Human Resources management; 

